### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core, forms

### Description

I would like to replace this implementation of `ControlValueAccessor` with new `input signals api`

```typescript
@Directive()
export abstract class InputAbstractComponent<T> implements ControlValueAccessor {
  public readonly componentId = this.constructor.name.toLowerCase();
  public static nextId = 0;
  public abstract id: string;
  public onChange: (_: T) => void = () => {};
  public onTouched: () => void = () => {};

  @Input({ transform: booleanAttribute }) public required!: boolean;
  @Input({ transform: booleanAttribute }) public disabled!: boolean;

  public abstract writeValue(value: T): void;

  public registerOnChange(fn: (_: T) => void): void {
    this.onChange = fn;
  }
  public registerOnTouched(fn: () => void): void {
    this.onTouched = fn;
  }
  public setDisabledState?(isDisabled: boolean): void {
    this.disabled = isDisabled;
  }
  public validate(_: FormControl): ValidationErrors | null {
    return _.valid ? null : { [this.componentId]: { valid: false, message: this.componentId } };
  }
}
```

### Proposed solution

I have tried to use new api like this:

```typescript
@Directive()
export abstract class InputAbstractComponent<T> implements ControlValueAccessor {
  public readonly componentId = this.constructor.name.toLowerCase();
  public static nextId = 0;
  public abstract id: string;
  public onChange: (_: T) => void = () => {};
  public onTouched: () => void = () => {};

  public required = input(false, { transform: booleanAttribute });
  public disabled = input(false, { transform: booleanAttribute }); // <---

  public abstract writeValue(value: T): void;

  public registerOnChange(fn: (_: T) => void): void {
    this.onChange = fn;
  }
  public registerOnTouched(fn: () => void): void {
    this.onTouched = fn;
  }
  public setDisabledState?(isDisabled: boolean): void {
    this.disabled.set(isDisabled); // <---
  }
  public validate(_: FormControl): ValidationErrors | null {
    return _.valid ? null : { [this.componentId]: { valid: false, message: this.componentId } };
  }
}
```

but unfortunately...

```typescript
Property 'set' does not exist on type 'InputSignal<boolean, unknown>'
```

probably because input signal is not writable...


### Alternatives considered

Do not use disabled as input... but as I can see here:

https://github.com/angular/components/blob/main/src/material/radio/radio.ts#L216

or here:

https://github.com/angular/components/blob/main/src/material/datepicker/datepicker-input-base.ts#L96

... still it is a good practice

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

I am currentely trying to use new `input signal api` but I am unable to replace this code with DRY.

```typescript
  @HostBinding('attr.title')
  @Input({ required: true, alias: 'appModalClose' })
  public closeBtnText!: string;
```


### Proposed solution

Maybe it should be replaced by something like

```typescript
public closeBtnText = input.required<string>({ alias: 'appModalClose', hostBinding: ['attr.title'] });
```

### Alternatives considered

I was trying to find some solutions, but this is not working

1. 

```typescript
@HostBinding('attr.title')
public closeBtnText = input.required<string>({ alias: 'appModalClose' });
```

2. Host is stacked in memory leak

```typescript
@Component({
  // eslint-disable-next-line @angular-eslint/no-host-metadata-property
  host: {
    '[title]': 'closeBtnText()',
  },
})
export class ModalCloseComponent {
  public closeBtnText = input.required<string>({ alias: 'appModalClose' });
}
```

