### Description

I read source code and know when injector set to null use `injectRootLimpMode` ,so I test runInjectionContext as follows
![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/9607121/413ac591-a0c1-4e61-b368-37223fd81f10)

```ts
 effect(() => {
        runInInjectionContext(null as any, () => {
          let aa = inject(DATA);
          console.log('value', aa);
        });
      });
```
It worked now.
Because I used 'any', I am not sure if it meets the official design requirements
If allowed, can type `null` be added?
I hope this design can be adopted because it allows' effect 'to read global variables from anywhere





